1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,304
Psalm 45.

2
00:00:02,304 --> 00:00:09,240
My heart is inditing a good matter: I speak of the things which I have made touching the king: my tongue is the pen of

3
00:00:09,240 --> 00:00:11,160
a ready writer.

4
00:00:11,160 --> 00:00:17,736
Thou art fairer than the children of men: grace is poured into thy lips: therefore God hath blessed thee for ever.

5
00:00:17,736 --> 00:00:23,016
Gird thy sword upon thy thigh, O most mighty, with thy glory and thy majesty.

6
00:00:23,016 --> 00:00:29,784
And in thy majesty ride prosperously because of truth and meekness and righteousness; and thy right hand shall teach

7
00:00:29,784 --> 00:00:37,320
thee terrible things. Thine arrows are sharp in the heart of the king’s enemies; whereby the people fall under thee.

8
00:00:37,320 --> 00:00:42,960
Thy throne, O God, is for ever and ever: the sceptre of thy kingdom is a right sceptre.

9
00:00:42,960 --> 00:00:50,328
Thou lovest righteousness, and hatest wickedness: therefore God, thy God, hath anointed thee with the oil of gladness

10
00:00:50,328 --> 00:00:52,512
above thy fellows.

11
00:00:52,512 --> 00:01:00,312
All thy garments smell of myrrh, and aloes, and cassia, out of the ivory palaces, whereby they have made thee glad.

12
00:01:00,312 --> 00:01:06,264
Kings’ daughters were among thy honourable women: upon thy right hand did stand the queen in gold of Ophir.

13
00:01:06,264 --> 00:01:14,952
Hearken, O daughter, and consider, and incline thine ear; forget also thine own people, and thy father’s house; So shall

14
00:01:14,952 --> 00:01:20,232
the king greatly desire thy beauty: for he is thy Lord; and worship thou him.

15
00:01:20,232 --> 00:01:26,232
And the daughter of Tyre shall be there with a gift; even the rich among the people shall intreat thy favour.

16
00:01:26,232 --> 00:01:31,152
The king’s daughter is all glorious within: her clothing is of wrought gold.

17
00:01:31,152 --> 00:01:37,800
She shall be brought unto the king in raiment of needlework: the virgins her companions that follow her shall be brought

18
00:01:37,800 --> 00:01:44,880
unto thee. With gladness and rejoicing shall they be brought: they shall enter into the king’s palace.

19
00:01:44,880 --> 00:01:50,328
Instead of thy fathers shall be thy children, whom thou mayest make princes in all the earth.

20
00:01:50,328 --> 00:01:56,736
I will make thy name to be remembered in all generations: therefore shall the people praise thee for ever and ever.

21
00:01:56,736 --> 00:02:06,600
Galatians 1. Paul, an apostle, (not of men, neither by man, but by Jesus Christ, and God the Father, who raised him from

22
00:02:06,600 --> 00:02:08,928
the dead;)

23
00:02:08,928 --> 00:02:16,200
And all the brethren which are with me, unto the churches of Galatia: Grace be to you and peace from God the Father, and

24
00:02:16,200 --> 00:02:23,207
from our Lord Jesus Christ, Who gave himself for our sins, that he might deliver us from this present evil world,

25
00:02:23,207 --> 00:02:29,568
according to the will of God and our Father: To whom be glory for ever and ever. Amen.

26
00:02:29,568 --> 00:02:36,408
I marvel that ye are so soon removed from him that called you into the grace of Christ unto another gospel: Which is not

27
00:02:36,408 --> 00:02:41,423
another; but there be some that trouble you, and would pervert the gospel of Christ.

28
00:02:41,423 --> 00:02:48,263
But though we, or an angel from heaven, preach any other gospel unto you than that which we have preached unto you, let

29
00:02:48,263 --> 00:02:50,327
him be accursed.

30
00:02:50,327 --> 00:02:58,031
As we said before, so say I now again, If any man preach any other gospel unto you than that ye have received, let him

31
00:02:58,031 --> 00:03:05,184
be accursed. For do I now persuade men, or God? or do I seek to please men?

32
00:03:05,184 --> 00:03:09,504
for if I yet pleased men, I should not be the servant of Christ.

33
00:03:09,504 --> 00:03:15,288
But I certify you, brethren, that the gospel which was preached of me is not after man.

34
00:03:15,288 --> 00:03:21,384
For I neither received it of man, neither was I taught it, but by the revelation of Jesus Christ.

35
00:03:21,384 --> 00:03:28,560
For ye have heard of my conversation in time past in the Jews’ religion, how that beyond measure I persecuted the church

36
00:03:28,560 --> 00:03:35,808
of God, and wasted it: And profited in the Jews’ religion above many my equals in mine own nation, being more

37
00:03:35,808 --> 00:03:39,480
exceedingly zealous of the traditions of my fathers.

38
00:03:39,480 --> 00:03:46,728
But when it pleased God, who separated me from my mother’s womb, and called me by his grace, To reveal his Son in me,

39
00:03:46,728 --> 00:03:53,616
that I might preach him among the heathen; immediately I conferred not with flesh and blood: Neither went I up to

40
00:03:53,616 --> 00:04:00,408
Jerusalem to them which were apostles before me; but I went into Arabia, and returned again unto Damascus.

41
00:04:00,408 --> 00:04:06,696
Then after three years I went up to Jerusalem to see Peter, and abode with him fifteen days.

42
00:04:06,696 --> 00:04:11,184
But other of the apostles saw I none, save James the Lord’s brother.

43
00:04:11,184 --> 00:04:16,512
Now the things which I write unto you, behold, before God, I lie not.

44
00:04:16,512 --> 00:04:23,880
Afterwards I came into the regions of Syria and Cilicia; And was unknown by face unto the churches of Judaea which were

45
00:04:23,880 --> 00:04:25,632
in Christ:

46
00:04:25,632 --> 00:04:32,232
But they had heard only, That he which persecuted us in times past now preacheth the faith which once he destroyed.

47
00:04:32,232 --> 00:04:34,704
And they glorified God in me.

